---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Craziest Upsets We Could See in the Group Stage" description="With Africa getting 9 slots and Asia getting 8, the global south is coming to crash the party.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-[#F7803C]">
    <article class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl bg-white border-[4px] border-black p-8 md:p-12 shadow-[12px_12px_0px_#2E0D23] relative z-20">
      <div class="inline-block bg-yellow-300 text-black border-[3px] border-black font-black px-4 py-1 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">PREDICTIONS</div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-6 leading-none" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        The Craziest Upsets We Could See in the Group Stage
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-black font-medium leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-black border-l-8 border-l-blue-600">
          With the 48-team expansion, the global south is arriving in full force. The old guard of European and South American dominance is shaking. Here are the dark horses ready to ruin brackets.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">1. The Next Morocco</h2>
        <p>
          Africa has 9 guaranteed spots now (up from 5). Teams like Senegal, Ivory Coast, and Nigeria have rosters stacked with players who start every week in the Premier League and Serie A. If Nigeria’s attack clicks, they could easily dismantle a sluggish European favorite in the group stages. They aren't just here to participate; they are here to take scalps.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">2. Asian Giants Leveling Up</h2>
        <p>
          Asia now gets 8 spots. Japan and South Korea already proved in 2022 that they can beat teams like Germany and Portugal. But watch out for the second tier of Asian teams like Saudi Arabia (who beat eventual winners Argentina in 2022). With the tactical discipline we're seeing across AFC, expect at least two massive upsets from this region.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mt-12 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">3. CONCACAF Home Field Buff</h2>
        <p>
          Don't sleep on the home continent advantage. Yes, USA, Mexico, and Canada are hosts. But teams like Panama or Costa Rica will have massive diasporas backing them in US stadiums. It will feel like a home game for them. When you combine that crowd energy with high-stakes Matchday 3 drama, a massive giant-killing is inevitable.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-blue-100 border-[3px] border-black shadow-[4px_4px_0px_#2E0D23]">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-2">TL;DR:</h3>
          <p class="font-bold">The gap between the "elites" and the rest of the world has officially closed. Expect the Round of 32 to feature teams you never thought you'd see survive the groups.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-between items-center border-t-[4px] border-black pt-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="font-outfit text-xl uppercase text-black hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">← Back to Guides</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
